Package: CharAnalysis
Type: Package
Title: Diagnostic and Analytical Tools for Peak Analysis in
    Sediment-Charcoal Records
Version: 2.0.0
Date: 2026-04-07
Authors@R: person("Philip", "Higuera",
    email   = "philip.higuera@umontana.edu",
    role    = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1278-4095"))
Description: Diagnostic and analytical tools for reconstructing local
    fire histories from lake-sediment charcoal records using peak
    detection. CharAnalysis decomposes a charcoal accumulation rate
    (CHAR) time series into low-frequency background (C_background) and
    high-frequency peak (C_peak) components, identifies charcoal peaks
    that likely represent fire events using either a global or local
    sliding-window threshold, applies a minimum-count significance
    screen, and summarises fire-history metrics including fire-return
    intervals, Weibull statistics, and smoothed fire frequency. Since
    its original development in the mid-2000s, CharAnalysis has been
    used in dozens of published studies to analyse sediment-charcoal
    records worldwide. This R package is a translation of CharAnalysis
    Version 2.0 (MATLAB) and produces quantitatively equivalent results
    on validated reference datasets; minor numerical differences in peak
    detection may occur due to floating-point divergence in the Gaussian
    mixture model. A companion MATLAB implementation is available at the
    same repository. The entire codebase is openly distributed and well
    commented — users are encouraged to explore the source, understand
    the underlying methods, and modify the package to suit individual
    needs. See Higuera et al. (2009) <doi:10.1890/07-2019.1> for the
    underlying methodology.
